Info for The Beatles 1967 – 1970 (2023 Edition)


Digitally remastered! The Beatles took the micky from 1967-70, making the greatest songs ever committed and then just buggering off, luckily they left us some of the great albums of our times and a compilation so full of bangers they had to split it into two-eras. The 'Blue Album' is Beatles in empirical album mode, their finest stage. This new edition features remastered editions and an additional 9 tracks not on the original, including a NEW Beatles track (which i'll let you make your mind up on).

This landmark compilation has introduced generations of fans to the incredible history of the most storied band in music. For its 50th anniversary, the collection has been expanded with 9 additional tracks, including “Blackbird”, “Glass Onion” and the new song, “Now And Then”. The last Beatles song, “Now And Then” completes John Lennon’s 1970s vocal and piano demo recording with parts played by Paul McCartney, George Harrison and Ringo Starr, as well as a new arrangement for strings.
